page.title: 10ECOLOGY OF WIMBOLDSLEY
page.content: There are badgers, squirrels and foxes near the school.Some get run over. There are squirrels' dreys and magpie nests in the wood over the road. We see them popping back and to.There are hedgehogs and badgers which just go across the road without looking.There is a moorhen and babies in the pond in the wood.We have a pond in the school field with frogs, newts and insects. {THE WOOD} Squirrels look for nuts. People dump their rubbish. Moorhens! A big pit with water in it. Dried up in summer. Lots of wild flowers. Mainly oak trees. {STONEY PATH.}Wild flowers grow here protected by a high hedge from the weedkiller sprays.In some places it is muddy.I got my welly stuck in a hole.
